tomation#Anti-Patterns#❌ Single Browser Context for Everything":[53,54],"#Browser Automation#⚠️ Sharp Edges":[55,67],"#Browser Automation#⚠️ Sharp Edges#{1}":[57,67],"#Browser Automation#Related Skills":[68,71],"#Browser Automation#Related Skills#{1}":[70,71]},"outlinks":[],"metadata":{"name":"browser-automation","description":"Browser automation powers web testing, scraping, and AI agent interactions. The difference between a flaky script and a reliable system comes down to understanding selectors, waiting strategies, and anti-detection patterns.  This skill covers Playwright (recommended) and Puppeteer, with patterns for testing, scraping, and agentic browser control. Key insight: Playwright won the framework war. Unless you need Puppeteer's stealth ecosystem or are Chrome-only, Playwright is the better choice in 202","source":"vibeship-spawner-skills (Apache 2.0)"},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"key":"00_System/Links/App_agent_skills_repo/browser-automation/SKILL.md"},
